article.headline: Auburn 66, Texas-Pan American 63
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- DeWayne Reed scored 14 points and made two free throws with 16 seconds left to help Auburn beat Texas-Pan American 66-63 on Tuesday night. The Tigers (13-7) jumped out to a 14-0 lead and a 39-28 halftime advantage, but needed 7 of 10 free throws in the final 2:04 to hang on for the nonconference win. The Broncs (5-13), who have lost six of seven, went on a 19-7 run for their first lead at 47-46 with 9:26 left. The Tigers regained the edge at 52-51 and built a five-point cushion. P.J. Turner's three-point play with 17 seconds left pulled Texas-Pan American within two. After Reed's two foul shots for 65-61, Turner made a layup. Quantez Robertson then hit a free throw to seal the win for Auburn, which is 11-2 at home. Korvotney Barber had nine points and 10 rebounds for the Tigers. Turner led the Broncs with 16 points.
